{
    "content": "The Supplication of the Attributes.\r\n\r\nThis supplication is also called Dua al-Shubur. It is advisable to say this supplication at the last hour of Fridays. It is well-known that Dua al-Simat is one of the famous supplications, which was regularly said by the past scholars. This supplication is recorded in Shaykh al-Tusi’s book of Misbah al-Mutahajjid, Sayyid Ibn Tawus’s book of Jamal al-Usbu’, and al-Kaf’ami’s books through an authentic series of narrators on the authority of Muhammad ibn ‘Uthman al-’Umari, one of the Four Envoys of Imam al-Mahdi, peace be upon him. The supplication has been also reported from Imam Muhammad al-Baqir and Imam Ja’far al-Sadiq, peace be upon them. With commentary, al-Majlisi has also narrated the supplication in his famous book of Bihar al-Anwar. The following form is quoted from Shaykh al-Tusi’sMisbah al-Mutahajjid:\r\n\r\n--اَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّي اَسْاَلُكَ بِاسْمِكَ العَظِيْمِ الْاَعْظَمِ الْاَعَزِّ الْاَجَلِّ الْاَكْرَمِ الَّذِيْ اِذَا دُعِيْتَ بِهِ عَلىٰ مَغَالِقِ اَبْوَابِ السَّماۤءِ لِلْفَتْحِ بِالرَّحْمَةِ انْفَتَحَتْ، وَ اِذَا دُعِيْتَ بِهِ عَلىٰ مَضَاۤئِقِ اَبْوَابِ الْاَرْضِ لِلْفَرَجِ انْفَرَجَتْ وَاِذَا دُعِيْتَ بِهِ عَلىٰ العُسْرِ لِلْيُسْرِ تَيَسَّرَتْ وَاِذَا دُعِيْتَ بِهِ عَلىٰ الْاَمْوَاتِ لِلنُّشُوْرِ انْتَشَرَتْ وَاِذَا دُعِيْتَ بِهِ عَلىٰ كَشْفِ الْبَأْساۤءِ وَالضَّرَّاۤءِ انْكَشَفَتْ وَبِجَلَالِ وَجْهِكَ الْكَرِيْمِ اَكْرَمِ الْوُجُوْهِ وَاَعَزِّ الْوُجُوْهِ الَّذِيْ عَنَتْ لَهُ الْوُجُوْهُ وَخَضَعَتْ لَهُ الرِّقَابُ، وَخَشَعَتْ لَهُ الْاَصْوَاتُ وَ وَجِلَتْ لَهُ الْقُلُوْبُ مِنْ مَخَافَتِكَ، وَبِقُوَّتِكَ الَّتِيْ بِہَا تُمْسِكُ السَّمَاۤءَ اَنْ تَقَعَ عَلىٰ الْاَرْضِ اِلَّا بِاِذْنِكَ، وَتُمْسِكُ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْاَرْضَ اَنْ تَزُوْلَا، وَبِمَشِيَّتِكَ الَّتِيْ دَانَ لَهَا الْعَالَمُوْنَ، وَبِكَلِمَتِكَ الَّتِيْ خَلَقْتَ بِهَا السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْاَرْضَ وَبِحِكْمَتِكَ الَّتِيْ صَنَعْتَ بِهَا الْعَجَاۤئِبَ، وَخَلَقْتَ بِهَا الظُّلْمَةَ وَجَعَلْتَهَا لَيْلًا وَجَعَلْتَ اللَّيْلَ سَكَنًا، وَخَلَقْتَ بِهَا النُّورَ وَجَعَلْتَهٗ نَهَارًا، وَجَعَلْتَ النَّهَارَ نُشُوْرًا مُبْصِرًا، وَخَلَقْتَ بِهَا الشَّمْسَ وَجَعَلْتَ الشَّمْسَ ضِيَاۤءً، وَخَلَقْتَ بِهَا الْقَمَرَ وَجَعَلْتَ الْقَمَرَ نُورًا، وَخَلَقْتَ بِهَا الْكَوَاكِبَ وَجَعَلْتَهَا نُجُوْمًا وَبُرُوْجًا وَمَصَابِيْحَ وَزِيْنَةً وَ رُجُوْمًا، وَجَعَلْتَ لَهَا مَشَارِقَ وَمَغَارِبَ، وَجَعَلْتَ لَهَا مَطَالِعَ وَمَجَارِيْ، وَجَعَلْتَ لَهَا فَلْكًا وَمَسَابِحَ، وَقَدَّرْتَهَا فِي السَّمَاۤءِ مَنَازِلَ فَاَحْسَنْتَ تَقْدِيْرَهَا، وَصَوَّرْتَهَا فَاَحْسَنْتَ تَصْوِيْرَهَا وَاَحْصَيْتَهَا بِاَسْمَاۤئِكَ اِحْصَاۤءً وَ دَبَّرْتَهَا بِحِكْمَتِكَ تَدْبِيْرًا وَاَحْسَنْتَ تَدْبِيْرَهَا، وَسَخَّرْتَهَا بِسُلْطَانِ اللَّيْلِ وَسُلْطَانِ النَّهَارِ وَالسَّاعَاتِ وَعَدَدِ السِّنِيْنَ وَالْحِسَابَ وَجَعَلْتَ رُؤْيَتَهَا لِجَمِيْعِ النَّاسِ مَرْئً وَاحِدًا، وَاَسْاَلُكَ اللّٰهُمَّ بِمَجْدِكَ الَّذِيْ كَلَّمْتَ بِهِ عَبْدَكَ وَرَسُوْلَكَ مُوْسىٰ بْنَ عِمْرَانَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلَامُ فِى الْمُقَدَّسِيْنَ فَوْقَ اِحْسَاسِ الْكَرُوْبِيْنَ فَوْقَ غَمَاۤئِمِ النُّوْرِ فَوْقَ تَابُوْتِ الشَّهَادَةِ فِيْ عَمُوْدِ النَّارِ وَ فِيْ طُوْرِ سَيْنَاۤءَ وَ فِيْ جَبَلِ حُوْرِيْثَ فِيْ الْوَادِ الْمُقَدَّسِ فِيْ الْبُقْعَةِ الْمُبَارَكَةِ مِنْ جَانِبِ الطُّوْرِ الْاَيْمَنِ مِنَ الشَّجَرَةِ وَ فِيْ اَرْضِ مِصْرَ بِتِسْعِ اٰيَاتٍ بَيِّنَاتٍ وَ يَوْمَ فَرَقْتَ لِبَنِىْ اِسْرَاۤئِيْلَ الْبَحْرَ وَ فِيْ الْمُنْبَجِسَاتِ الَّتِىْ صَنَعْتَ بِهَا الْعَجَاۤئِبَ فِيْ بَحْرِ سُوْفِ وَ عَقَدْتَ مَاۤءَ الْبَحْرِ فِيْ قَلْبِ الْغَمْرِ كَالْحِجَارَةِ وَ جَاوَزْتَ بِبَنِىْ اِسْرَاۤئِيْلَ الْبَحْرَ وَ تَمَّتْ كَلِمَتُكَ الْحُسْنىٰ عَلَيْهِمْ بِمَا صَبَرُوْا وَ اَوْرَثْتَهُمْ مَشَارِقَ الْاَرْضِ وَ مَغَارِبِهَا الَّتِىْ بَارَكْتَ فِيْهَا لِلْعَالَمِيْنَ وَ اَغْرَقْتَ فِرْعَوْنَ وَ جُنُوْدَهُ وَ مَرَاكِبَهُ فِيْ الْيَمِّ وَ بِاسْمِكَ الْعَظِيْمِ الْاَعْظَمِ الْاَعَزِّ الْاَجَلِّ الْاَكْرَمِ وَ بِمَجْدِكَ الَّذِىْ تَجَلَّيْتَ بِهِ لِمُوْسىٰ كَلِيْمِكَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فِيْ طُوْرِ سَيْنَاۤءِ وَ لِاِبْرَاهِيْمَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ خَلِيْلِكَ مِنْ قَبْلُ فِىْ مَسْجِدِ الْخَيْفِ وَ لِاِسْحَاقَ صَفِيِّكَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فِىْ بِئْرِ شِيَعِ وَ لِيَعْقُوْبَ نَبِيِّكَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فِىْ بَيْتِ اِيْلٍ وَ اَوْفَيْتَ لِاِبْرَاهِيْمَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ بِمِيْثَاقِكَ وَ لِاِسْحَاقَ بِحَلْفِكَ وَ لِيَعْقُوْبَ بِشَهَادَتِكَ وَ لِلْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ بِوَعْدِكَ وَ لِلدَّاعِيْنَ بِاَسْمَاۤئِكَ فَاَجَبْتَ وَ بِمَجْدِكَ الَّذِىْ ظَهَرَ لِمُوْسَى بْنِ عِمْرَانَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ عَلىٰ قُبَّةِ الرُّمَّانِ وَ بِاٰيَاتِكَ الَّتِى وَقَعَتْ عَلىٰ اَرْضِ مِصْرَ بِمَجْدِ الْعِزَّةٍ وَ الْغَلَبَةِ بِاٰيَاتِ عَزِيْزَةٌ وَ بِسُلْطَانِ الْقُوَّةِ وَ بِعِزَّةِ الْقُدْرَةِ وَ بِشَأْنِ الْكَلِمَةِ التَّامَّةِ وَ بِكَلِمَاتِكَ الَّتِى تَفَضَّلْتَ بِهَا عَلىٰ اَهْلِ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَ الْاَرْضِ وَ اَهْلِ الدُّنْيَا وَ اَهْلِ الْاٰخِرَةِ وَ بِرَحْمَتِكَ الَّتِىْ مَنَنْتَ بِهَا عَلىٰ جَمِيْعِ خَلْقِكَ وَ بِاسْتِطَاعَتِكَ الَّتِىْ اَقَمْتَ بِهَا عَلىٰ الْعَالَمِيْنَ وَ بِنُوْرِكَ الَّذِىْ قَدْ خَرَّ مِنْ فَزَعِهِ طُوْرُ سَيْنَاۤءَ وَ بِعِلْمِكَ وَ جَلَالِكَ وَ كِبْرِيَاۤئِكَ وَ عِزَّتِكَ وَ جَبَرُوْتِكَ الَّتِىْ لَمْ تَسْتَقِلَّهَا الْاَرْضُ وَ انْخَفَضَتْ لَهَا السَّمَاوَاتُ وَ انْزَجَرَ لَهَا الْعُمْقُ الْاَكْبَرُ وَ رَكَدَتْ لَهَا الْبِحَارُ وَ الْاَنْهارُ وَ خَضَعَتْ لَهَا الْجِبَالُ وَ سَكَنَتْ لَهَا الْاَرْضُ بِمَنَاكِبِهَا وَ اسْتَسْلَمَتْ لَهَا الْخَلَاۤئِقُ كُلُّهَا وَ خَفَقَتْ لَهَا الرِّيَاحُ فِى جَرَيَانِهَا وَ خَمَدَتْ لَهَا النِّيْرَانُ فِىْ اَوْطَانِهَا وَ بِسُلْطَانِكَ الَّذِىْ عُرِفَتْ لَكَ بِهِ الْغَلَبَةُ دَهْرَ الدُّهُوْرِ وَ حُمِدْتَ بِهِ فِى السَّمَاوَاتِ وَ الْاَرَضِيْنَ وَ بِكَلِمَتِكَ كَلِمَةِ الصِّدْقِ الَّتِىْ سَبَقَتْ لِاَبِيْنَا اٰدَمَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ وَ ذُرِّيَّتِهِ بِالرَّحْمَةِ وَ اَسْئَلُكَ بِكَلِمَتِكَ الَّتِىْ غَلَبَتْ كُلَّ شَىْءٍ وَ بِنُوْرِ وَجْهِكَ الَّذِىْ تَجَلَّيْتَ بِهِ لِلْجَبَلِ فَجَعَلْتَهُ دَكًّا وَ خَرَّ مُوْسىٰ صَعِقًا وَ بِمَجْدِكَ الَّذِىْ ظَهَرَ عَلىٰ طُوْرِ سَيْناۤءِ فَكَلَّمْتَ بِهِ عَبْدَكَ وَ رَسُوْلَكَ مُوْسَى بْنَ عِمْرَانَ وَ بِطَلْعَتِكَ فِىْ سَاعِيْرَ وَ ظُهُوْرِكَ فِىْ جَبَلِ فَارَانَ بِرَبَوَاتِ الْمُقَدَّسِيْنَ وَ جُنُوْدِ الْمَلَاۤئِكَةِ الصَّافِّيْنَ وَ خُشُوْعِ الْمَلَاۤئِكَةِ الْمُسَبِّحِيْنَ وَ بِبَرَكَاتِكَ الَّتِىْ بَارَكْتَ فِيْهَا عَلىٰ اِبْرَاهِيْمَ خَلِيْلِكَ عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ فِىْ اُمَّةِ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهِ وَ بَارَكْتَ لِاِسْحَاقَ صَفِيِّكَ فِىْ اُمَّةِ عِيْسىٰ عَلَيْهِمَا السَّلَامُ وَ بَارَكْتَ لِيَعْقُوْبَ اِسْرَاۤئِيْلِكَ فِىْ اُمَّةِ مُوْسىٰ عَلَيْهِمَاالسَّلَامُ وَ بَارَكْتَ لِحَبِيْبِكَ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهِ فِىْ عِتْرَتِهِ وَ ذُرِّيَّتِهِ وَ اُمَّتِهِ اَللّٰهُمَّ وَ كَمَا غِبْنَا عَنْ ذٰلِكَ وَ لَمْ نَشْهَدْهُ وَ اٰمَنَّا بِهِ وَ لَمْ نَرَهُ صِدْقًا وَ عَدْلًا اَنْ تُصَلِّىَ عَلىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اَنْ تُبَارِكَ عَلىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ تَرَحَّمَ عَلىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ كَاَفْضَلِ مَا صَلَّيْتَ وَ بَارَكْتَ وَ تَرَحَّمْتَ عَلىٰ اِبْرَاهِيْمَ وَ اٰلِ اِبْرَاهِيْمَ اِنَّكَ حَمِيْدٌ مَجِيْدٌ فَعَّالٌ لِمَا تُرِيْدُ وَ اَنْتَ عَلىٰ كُلِّ شَىْءٍ قَدِيْرٌ۔--You may now beseech Almighty Allah to grant you your personal requests. Then, say the following:\r\n\r\n--يَا اَللهُ يَا حَنَّانُ يَا مَنَّانُ يَا بَدِيْعَ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَ الْاَرْضِ يَا ذَا الْجَلَالِ وَ الْاِكْرَامِ يَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِيْنَ--According to some copies of the supplication, the following statement is added before the latter portion:\r\n\r\n--يَا اَللهُ يَا حَنَّانُ يَا مَنَّانُ يَا بَدِيْعَ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَ الْاَرْضِ يَا ذَا الْجَلَالِ وَ الْاِكْرَامِ يَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِيْنَ اَللّٰهُمَّ بِحَقِّ هٰذَا الدُّعَاۤءِ وَ بِحَقِّ هٰذِهِ الْاَسْمَاۤءِ الَّتِىْ لَا يَعْلَمُ تَفْسِيْرَهَا وَ لَا تَأْوِيْلَهَا وَ لَا بَاطِنَهَا وَ لَا ظَاهِرَهَا غَيْرُكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّىَ عَلىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اَنْ تَرْزُقَنِىْ خَيْرَ الدُّنْيَا وَ الْاٰخِرَةِ--Shaykh al-Majlisi has quoted Sayyid Ibn Baqi as saying, in al-Misbah, that the following supplicatory prayer is advisably said after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\n--اَللّٰهُمَّ بِحَقِّ هٰذَا الدُّعَاۤءِ وَ بِحَقِّ هٰذِهِ الْاَسْمَاۤءِ الَّتِىْ لَا يَعْلَمُ تَفْسِيْرَهَا وَ لَا تَأْوِيْلَهَا وَ لَا بَاطِنَهَا وَ لَا ظَاهِرَهَا غَيْرُكَ اَنْ تُصَلِّىَ عَلىٰ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اَنْ تَرْزُقَنِىْ خَيْرَ الدُّنْيَا وَ الْاٰخِرَةِ--You may then mention your need and continue as follows:\r\n\r\n--وَ افْعَلْ بِىْ مَا اَنْتَ اَهْلُهُ وَ لَا تَفْعَلْ بِىْ مَا اَنَا اَهْلُهُ وَ انْتَقِمْ لِىْ مِنْ فُلَانِ بْنِ فُلَانِ (اَعْدَاۤءِ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ)--You may here mention the name of your enemy\r\n\r\n--وَ اغْفِرْ لِىْ مِنْ ذُنُوْبِى مَا تَقَدَّمَ مِنْهَا وَ مَا تَاَخَّرَ وَ لِوَالِدَىَّ وَ لِجَمِيْعِ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ وَ وَسِّعْ عَلَىَّ مِنْ حَلَالِ رِزْقِكَ وَ اكْفِنِىْ مَؤُنَةَ اِنْسَانِ سَوْءٍ وَ جَارِ سَوْءٍ وَ سُلْطَانِ سَوْءٍ وَ قَرِيْنِ سَوْءٍ وَ يَوْمِ سَوْءٍ وَ سَاعَةِ سَوْءٍ وَ انْتَقِمْ لِىْ مِمَّنْ يَكِيْدُنِىْ وَ مِمَّنْ يَبْغِىْ عَلَىَّ وَ يُرِيْدُبِىْ وَ بِاَهْلِىْ وَ اَوْلَادِىْ وَ اِخْوَانِىْ وَ جِيْرَانِىْ وَ قَرَابَاتِى مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ ظُلْمًا اِنَّكَ عَلىٰ مَا تَشَاۤءُ قَدِيْرٌ وَ بِكُلِّ شَىْءٍ عَلِيْمٌ اٰمِيْنَ رَبَّ الْعَالَمِيْنَ۔--You may then say the following:\r\n\r\n--اَللّٰهُمَّ بِحَقِّ هٰذَا الدُّعَاۤءِ تَفَضَّلْ عَلىٰ فُقَرَاۤءِ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالْغِنىٰ وَ الثَّرْوَةِ وَ عَلىٰ مَرْضَى الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالشِّفَاۤءِ وَ الصِّحَةِ وَ عَلىٰ اَحْيَاۤءِ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِاللُّطْفِ وَ الْكَرَامَةِ وَ عَلىٰ اَمْوَاتِ الْمُؤمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالْمَغْفِرَةِ وَ الرَّحْمَةِ وَ عَلىٰ مُسَافِرِى الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالرَّدِّ اِلىٰ اَوْطَانِهِمْ سَالِمِيْنَ غَانِمِيْنَ بِرَحْمَتِكَ يَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِيْنَ وَ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلىٰ سَيِّدِنَا مُحَمَّدٍ خَاتَمِ النَّبِيِّيْنَ وَ عِتْرَتِهِ الطَّاهِرِيْنَ وَ سَلَّمَ تَسْلِيْمًا كَثِيْرًا۔--Shaykh Ibn Fahad says that it is recommended to say the following prayer after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\n--اَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّى اَسْئَلُكَ بِحُرْمَةِ هٰذَا الدُّعَاۤءِ وَ بِمَا فَاتَ مِنْهُ مِنَ الْاَسْمَاۤءِ وَ بِمَا يَشْتَمِلُ عَلَيْهِ مِنَ التَّفْسِيْرِ وَ التَّدْبِيْرِ الَّذِىْ لَا يُحِيْطُ بِهِ اِلَّا اَنْتَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ بِىْ ۔۔۔۔--You may now mention your personal needs.", 
    "audio": "http://www.ya-mahdi.net/apps_audio/simaat.mp3", 
    "transliteration": "The Supplication of the Attributes.\r\n\r\nThis supplication is also called Dua al-Shubur. It is advisable to say this supplication at the last hour of Fridays. It is well-known that Dua al-Simat is one of the famous supplications, which was regularly said by the past scholars. This supplication is recorded in Shaykh al-Tusi’s book of Misbah al-Mutahajjid, Sayyid Ibn Tawus’s book of Jamal al-Usbu’, and al-Kaf’ami’s books through an authentic series of narrators on the authority of Muhammad ibn ‘Uthman al-’Umari, one of the Four Envoys of Imam al-Mahdi, peace be upon him. The supplication has been also reported from Imam Muhammad al-Baqir and Imam Ja’far al-Sadiq, peace be upon them. With commentary, al-Majlisi has also narrated the supplication in his famous book of Bihar al-Anwar. The following form is quoted from Shaykh al-Tusi’s Misbah al-Mutahajjid:\r\n\r\nBISMILLAAHIR RAHMAANIR RAHEEM ALLAAHUMMA INNI AS-ALOKA BISMEKAL A'ZEEMIL A-A'ZAMIL A-A'ZZIL AJALLIL AKRAMIL LAZEE EZAA DO-EE'TA BEHI A'LAA MAGHAALEQE ABWAABIS SAMAAA-E LIL FATHE BIR-RAHMATIN FATAHAT WA EZAA DO-EE'TA BEHI A'LAA MAZAAA-EQE ABWAABIL ARZE LILFARAJIN FARAJAT, WA EZAA DO-EE'TA BEHI A'LAL U'SRE LIL-YUSRE TAYASSARAT, WA EZAA DO-EE'TA BEHI A'LAL AMWAATE LIN-NOSHOORIN TASHARAT, WA EZAA DO-EE'TA BEHI A'LAA KASHFIL BAA-SAAA-E WAZ-ZARRAAA-E INKASHAFAT, WA BE JALAALE WAJHEKAL KAREEME AKRAMIL WOJOOHE WA A-A'ZZIL WOJOOHIL LAZE A'NAT LAHUL WOJOOHO WA KHAZA-A'T LAHUR REQAABO WA KHASHA-A'T LAUL ASWAATO WA WAJELAT LAHUL QOLOOBO MIN MAKHAABATEKA, WA BE QUWWATEKAL LATEE BEHAA TUMSEKUS SAMAAA-A AN TAQA-A' A'LAL ARZE ILLAA BE-IZNEKA, WA TUMSEKUS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZA AN TAZOOLAA, WA BEMASHIYYATEKAL LATEE DAANA (KAANA) LAHAL A'AALAMOONA, WA BEKALEMAATEKAL LATEE KALAQTA BEHAS SAMAAWAATE WAL-ARZA, WA BEHIKMATEKAL LATEE SANA'TA BEHAL A'JAAA-EBA WA KHALAQTA BEHAZ ZULMATA WA JA-A'LTAHAA LAILAN WA JA-A'LTAL LAYLA SAKANAN (MASKANAN) WA KHALAQTA BEHAN NOORA WA JA-A'LTAHU NAHAARAN WA JA-A'LTAN NAHAARA NOSHOORAN MUBSERAN, WA KHALAQTA BEHASH SHAMSA WA JA-ALTASH SHAMSA ZEYAAA-AN, WA KHALAQTA BEHAL QAMARA WA JA-A'LTAL QAMARA NOORAN, WA KHALAQTA BEHAL KAWAAKEBA WA JA-A'LTAHAA NOJOOMAN WA BOROOJAN WA MASAABEEHA WA ZEENATAN WA ROJOOMAN, WA JA-ALTA LAHAA MASHAAREQA WA MAGHAAREBA WA JA-A'LTA LAHAA MATAALE-A' WA MAJAAREYA, WA JA-A'LTA LAHAA FALAKAN WA MASAABEHA WA QADDARTAHAA FIS SAMAAA-E MANAAZELA FA-AHSANTA TAQDEERAHAA, WA SAWWARTAHAA FA-AHSANTA TASWEERAHAA WA AH-SAYTAHAA BE-ASMAAA-EKA EHSAAA-AN WA DABBARTAHAA BE HIKMATEKA TADBEERAN FA-AHSANTA TADBEERAHAA WA SAKHKHARTAHAA BE SULTAANIL LAYLE WA SULTAANIN NAHAARE WAS-SAA-A'ATE WA A'DADAS SENEENA WAL-HESAABE, WA JA-A'LTA ROA-YATAHAA LE JAMEE-I'N NAASE MAR-AN WAAHEDAN WA AS-ALOKALLAAHUMMA BE HAMDEKAL LAZE KALLAMTA BEHI A'BDAKA WA RASOOLAKA MOOSAB NA I'MRAANA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO FIL MOQADDASEENA FAWQA EHSAASIL KARROOBEENA (KARROOBIYYEENA) FAWQA GHAMAAA-EMIN NOORE FAWQA TAABOOTISH SHAHAADATE FI A'MOODIN NAAARE WA FEE (WA ELAA) TORE SAYNAAA-A WA FEE JABALE HOOREESA FIL WAADIL MOQADDASE FIL BUQ-A'TIL MOBAARAKATE MIN JAANEBIT TOORIL AYMANE MENASH-SHAJARATE WA FEE ARZE MISRA BE-TIS-E' AAYAATIN BAYYENAATIN, WA YAWMA FARAQTA LE-BANI ISRAAA-EELAL BAHRA WA FIL MUNBAJESAATIL LATI SA-NA'TA BEHAL A'JAAA-EBA FEE BAHRE SOOF, WA A'QADAT MAAA-AL BAHRE FEE QALBIL GHAMRE KAL-HAJAARATE, WA JAA-WAZTA BE BANI ISRAAEELAL BAHRA WA TAMMAT KALEMATOKAL HUSNAA A'LAYHIM BEMAA SABAROO WA AWRASTAHUM MASHAAREQAL ARZE WA MAGHAAREBAHAL LATEE BAARAKTA FEEHAA LIL-A'ALAMEENA, WA AGHRAQTA FIRAWNA WA JONOODAHU WA MARAAKEBAHU FIL YAMME, WA BISMEKAL A'ZEEMIL A-A'ZAMIL A-A'ZZIL AJALLIL AKRAME WA BEMAJDEKAL LAZE TAJALLAYTA BEHI LE MOOSA KALEEMAKE A'LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE TORE SAYNAA-A, WA LE-IBRAAHEEMA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO KHALEELEKA MIN QABLO FEE MASJEDIL KHEEFE, WALE ISHAAQA SAFIYYEKA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE BEA-RE SHEE-I'N (SAB-I'N) WA LE YAA'QOOBA NABIYYEKA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE BAYTE EELIN, WA AWFAYTA LE-IBRAAHEEMA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO BE MEESHAAQEKA WA LE-ISHAAQA BE HALFEKA WA LE YAA'QOOBA BE SHAHADATEKA WA LIL-MOA-MENEENA BE WA'DEKA WA LIDDAA-EE'NA BE ASMAAEKA FA-AJABTA, WA BE MAJDEKAL LAZE ZAHARA LE MOOSABNE I'MRAANA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO A'LAA QUBBATIR RUMMAANE WA BE AAYAATEKAL LATEE WA QA-A'T A'LAA ARZE MISRA BE MAJDIL I'ZZATE WAL-GHALABATE BE AAYAATE A'ZEEZATE WA BE SULTAANIL QUWWATE WA BE-I'ZZATIL QUDRATE WA BE-SHAANIL KALEMATIT TEAMMATE, WA BE KALEMAATEKAL LATEE TAFAZZALTA BEHAA A'LAA AHLIS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZE WA AHLID DUNYAA WA AHLIL AAKHERATE, WA BE RAHMATEKAL LATEE MANANTA BEHAA A'LAA JAMEE-E' KHALQEKA, WA BIS-TETAA-A'TEKAL LATEE AQAMTA BEHAA A'LAL A'ALAMEENA, WA BE NOOREKAL LAZEE QAD KHARRA MIN FAZA-E'HI TOORO SAYNAAA-A, WA BE-I'LMEKA WA JALAALEKA WA KIBREYAAA-EKA WA I'ZZATEKA WA JABAROOTEKAL LATEE LAM TASTAQILLAHAL ARZO WAN-KHAFAZAT LAHAS SAMAAWAATO WAN-ZAJARA LAHAL U'MQUL AKBARO, WA RAKADAT LAHAL BEHAARO WAL ANHAARO, WA KHAZA-A'T LAHAL JEBAALO WA SAKANAT LAHAL ARZO BE MANAAKEBEHAA, WAS-TASLAMAT LAHAL KHALAA-EQO KULLOHAA, WA KHAFAQAT LAHAR REYAAHO FI JARAYAANEHAA, WA KHAMADAT LAHAN NEERAANO FEE AWTAANEHAA, WA BE SULTAANEKAL LAZE O'REFAT LAKA BEHIL GHALABATO DAHRAD DOHOORE WA HOMID-TA BEHI FIS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARAZEENA, WA BEKALEMATEKA KALEMATIS SIDQIL LATEE SABAQAT LE-ANBEENAA AADAMA A'LAYHIS SALAAMO WA ZURRIYYATEHI BIR-RAHMATE WA AS-ALOKA BE KALEMATEKAL LATEE GHALABAT KULLA SHAY-IN, WA BE NOORE WAJHEKAL LAZEE TAJALLAYTA BEHI LIL JABALE FA-JA-A'LTAHU DAKKAA WA KHARRA MOOSAA SA-E'QAA, WA BE MAJDEKAL LAZEE ZAHARA A'LAA TORE SAYNAAA-A FA-KALLAMTA BEHI A'BDAKA WA RASOOLAKA MOOSABNE I'MRAANA, WA BE TAL-A'TEKA FEE SAA-E'ERA WA ZOHOOREKA FEE JABALE FAARAANA BE-RABAWAATIL MOQADDASEENA WA JONOODIL MALAAA-EKATIS SAAF-FEENA WA KHOSHOO-E'L MALAAA-EKATIL MOSABBEHEENA, WA BE-BARAKAATEKAL LATEE BAARAKTA FEEHAA A'LAA IBRAAHEEMA KHALEELEKA A'LAYHE WA AALEHI, WA BAARAKTA LE-ISHAAQA SAFIYYEKA FEE UMMATE E'ESAA A'LAYHEMAS SALAAMO, WA BAARAKTA LE YA'QOOBA ISRAAA-EELEKA FEE UMMATE MOOSAA A'LAYHEMAS SALAAMO, WA BAARAKTA LE HABIBEKA MOHAMMADIN SALLALLAAHO A'LAYHE WA AALEHI FEE I'TRATEHI WA ZURRIYYATEHI WA UMMATEHI, ALLAAHUMMA WA KAMAA GHIBNAA A'N ZAALEKA WA LAM NASH-HAD-HO WA AAMANNAA BEHI WA LAM NARAHU SIDQAN WA A'DLAA AN TOSALLAEYA A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN WA AN TOBAAREKA A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN WA TARAHHAMA A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN KA-AFZALE MAA SALLAYTA WA BAARAKTA WA TARAHHAMTA A'LAA IBRAAHEEMA WA AALE IBRAAHEEMA INNAKA HAMEEDUM MAJEEDUN FA-A'ALUL LEMAA TOREEDO WA ANTA A'LAA KULLE SHAY-IN QADEERUN.\r\n\r\nYou may now beseech Almighty Allah to grant you your personal requests. Then, say the following:\r\n\r\nYAA ALLAAHO YAA HANNAANO YAA MANNAANO YAA BADEE-A'S SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZE YAA ZAL-JALAALE WAL IKRAAME YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA\r\n\r\nAccording to some copies of the supplication, the following statement is added before the latter portion:\r\n\r\nYAA ALLAAHO YAA HANNAANO YAA MANNAANO YAA BADEE-A'S SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZE YAA ZAL-JALAALE WAL IKRAAME YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA ALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A'AA-E WA BE HAQQE HAAZEHIL ASMAAA-IL LATI LAA YA'LAMO TAFSEEROHAA WA LAA TAAWEELOHAA WALAA BAATENAHAA WA LAA ZAAHERAHAA GHAIROKA AN TOSALLE A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN WA AN TARZOQANEE KHARAD DUNYAA WAL AAKHERAH\r\n\r\nShaykh al-Majlisi has quoted Sayyid Ibn Baqi as saying, in al-Misbah, that the following supplicatory prayer is advisably said after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A'AA-E WA BE HAQQE HAAZEHIL ASMAAA-IL LATI LAA YA'LAMO TAFSEEROHAA WA LAA TAAWEELOHAA WALAA BAATENAHAA WA LAA ZAAHERAHAA GHAIROKA AN TOSALLE A'LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN WA AN TARZOQANEE KHARAD DUNYAA WAL AAKHERAH\r\n\r\nYou may then mention your need and continue as follows:\r\n\r\nWAF-A'L BEE MAA ANTA AHLOHU WA LAA TAF-A'L BEE MAA ANAA AHLOHU WANTAQIM LEE MIN FULAAN IBN FULAAN (A'ADAA-E AALE MOHAMMADIN)\r\n\r\nYou may here mention the name of your enemy…\r\n\r\nWAGHFIRLEE MIN ZONOOBI MAA TAQADDAMA MINHAA WA MAA AKH-KHARA WA LE WAALEDAYYA WA LE JAMEE-I'L MO-MENEENA WAL MOMENAATE WA WASSE' A'LAYYA MIN HALAALE RIZQEKA WAK-FENEE MAOONATA INSAANE SAW-IN WA SAA-A'TE SAW-IN WANTAQIM LEE MIMMAN YAKEEDONEE WA MIMMAN YABGHEE A'LAYYA WA YOREEDO BEE WA BE AHLEE WA AWLAADEE WA IKHWAANEE WA JEERAANI WA QARAABATI MENAL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE ZULMAN INNAKA A'LAA MAA TASHAAA-O QADEERUN WA BE KULLE SHAY'IN A'LEEMUN AAMEEN RABBAL A'AALAMEEN\r\n\r\nYou may then say the following:\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A'AA-E TAFAZZAL A'LAA FOQARAAA-IL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL GHENAA WAS SARWATE WA A'LAA MARZAL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BISH-SHEFAA-E WAS-SEHATE WA A'LAA AHYAAA-IL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL-LUTFE WAL KARAAMATE WA A'LAA AMWAATIL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL MAGHFERATE WAR-RAHMATE WA A'LAA MOSAAFERIL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIR-RADDE ELAA AWTAANEHIM SAALEMEENA GHAANEMEENA BE RAHMATEKA YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA WA SALLALLAAHO A'LAA SAYYEDENAA MOHAMMADIN KHAATAMIN NABIYYEENA WA I'TRATEHIT TAAHERAANA WA SALLAMA TASLEEMAN KASEERAN\r\n\r\nShaykh Ibn Fahad says that it is recommended to say the following prayer after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BE HURMATE HAAZEID-DO-A'AAA-E WA BEMAA FAATA MINHO MENAL AS-MAAA-E WA BEMAA YASHTAMELO A'LAYHE MENAT-TAFSEERE WAT-TADBEERIL LAZEE LAA YOHEETO BEHI ILLAA ANTA AN TAF-A'LA BEE KAZAA WA KAZAA.\r\n\r\nYou may now mention your personal needs.", 
    "english": "The Supplication of the Attributes.\r\n\r\nThis supplication is also called Dua al-Shubur. It is advisable to say this supplication at the last hour of Fridays. It is well-known that Dua al-Simat is one of the famous supplications, which was regularly said by the past scholars. This supplication is recorded in Shaykh al-Tusi’s book of Misbah al-Mutahajjid, Sayyid Ibn Tawus’s book of Jamal al-Usbu’, and al-Kaf’ami’s books through an authentic series of narrators on the authority of Muhammad ibn ‘Uthman al-’Umari, one of the Four Envoys of Imam al-Mahdi, peace be upon him. The supplication has been also reported from Imam Muhammad al-Baqir and Imam Ja’far al-Sadiq, peace be upon them. With commentary, al-Majlisi has also narrated the supplication in his famous book of Bihar al-Anwar. The following form is quoted from Shaykh al-Tusi’s Misbah al-Mutahajjid:\r\n\r\nIn the Name of Allah, the All-beneficent, the All-merciful. O Allah, I beseech You by Your Name, the most great, most majestic, most magnificent, and most noble; if You are besought thereby to open the closed doors of the sky, they will be opened with Your mercy, if You are besought thereby to remove the narrow doors of the heavens for relief, they will be opened wide, if You are besought thereby to make easy the difficulty, it will be easy, if You are besought thereby to restore the dead to life, they will rise from their graves, if You are besought thereby to remove misery and adversity, they will be removed. I also beseech You in the name of the Majesty of Your Noble Face; the Noblest and most Honored of all faces before Whom all faces bow down in submission, all necks bend down in reverence, all sounds yield, and all hearts tremble out of fear of You. I also beseech You by Your Might by which You prevent the sky from falling on the earth except with Your permission, and control the heavens and the earth so closely that they cannot move away from their positions, by Your Will, which the whole world obeys, by Your Word by which You have created the heavens and the earth, by Your Wisdom with which You have created the wonderful things, created darkness, made it night, made night the time of quiet and rest, created light, made it daylight, made day the time of movement and observation, created the sun, made the sun light, created the moon, made the moon of light, created heavenly bodies, made them fixed stars, planets, lamps for guidance at night, means of decoration, and missiles, created for them east and west, created for them places of ascendancy and orbits, created for them a firmament and spheres, fixed for them stages in the heaven with excellent fixing, shaped the stars with excellent shaping, measured them through Your Names with exact measurement, designed through Your wisdom a system for them with excellent design, controlled the heavenly bodies through the influence of night and the influence of day, and through hours, making them a means for the reckoning of years and counting, and made all people see them alike. I beseech You,O Allah, in the name of Your glory with which You addressed Your servant and Messenger, Moses the son of 'Imran ('a) while he was in the company of angels; an address even the favorite cherubim could not ever hear, above the clouds of light, above the box of evidence, within the pillar of fire on Mount Sinai and on Mount Hurith in the Holy Vale in the sacred tract of land to the right of Taurus Mountain through a tree, [and again addressed him] on the land of Egypt, after showing nine clear signs, and on the day You split the sea for the children of Israel, and caused springs to flow from a stone, thereby displaying wonders of Your might in a deep sea, on the day when You solidified the water of the sea in the midst of the storm, caused the children of Israel to pass by the sea, and fulfilled Your excellent promises made to them because of their calm endurance, made them the master of the East and the West in the earth wherein there are blessings for all the worlds, drowned Pharaoh, his armies, and boats in the water. [I beseech You] by Your Name, the great, the Most Great, the Most Honorable, Most Majestic, and Most Noble, and by Your Glory with which You revealed Yourself as light to Moses, Your addressee, peace be on him, on Mount Sinai, and earlier radiated the light for Abraham, Your sincere friend peace be on him, in the Mosque of al-Khif, and for Isaac, Your chosen Prophet, peace be on him, in Shi' Well, and for Your Prophet Jacob, peace be on him, in Bayt II, and You fulfilled Your promise to Abraham, peace be on him, Your oath in favor of Isaac, Your witnessing favoring Jacob, the fulfillments of Your promise to the faithful believers, and Your Names with which You accepted the prayers of supplicants, and by Your Glory, which appeared to Moses, the son of 'Imran, in al-Rumman Dome, and by Your Signs, which appeared in the land of Egypt with great might and victory, with powerful signs, with the display of full command, great power, the affair of the perfect word, and by Your words with which You do a favor to the inhabitants of the skies and the earth and the people of this world and the Next World, and by Your Mercy with which You bestow graces upon all Your creatures, and by Your Power with which You dominate the worlds, and by Your Light through fear of which Mount Sinai collapsed, and by Your Knowledge, Majesty, Greatness, Honor, and Might, which the earth could not bear, the heavens bent down, the great depths restrained themselves, oceans and rivers became stable, mountains yielded, the earth became firm on its shoulders, all creatures surrendered, the winds breathed in their flow, and the flaming fires were extinguished in their places, and by Your authority through which You are acknowledged to have All-powerfulness all the times and for which You are praised in the heavens and the earth, and by Your word, the Word of Truth, which had became mercy for our father Adam and his offspring, and by Your word that overcame everything, and by the light of Your Face, which when You showed to the Mount, You caused it to crush into pieces, whereby Moses fainted and fell down, and by Your Glory, which appeared on Mount Sinai, and through which You addressed Your servant and Messenger, Moses, the son of 'Imran, and by Your appearance in Sa'Ir, and by Your appearance on Mount Faran on the heights of the holy ones, When the troops of angels were in rows, and with the submissiveness of the angels glorifying You, and by Your blessings by which You honored Abraham, Your sincere friend ('a) among the people of Muhammad, Your blessings be upon him and his household, and You blessed Isaac, Your chosen prophet, among the followers of Jesus, peace be on them both, and You blessed Jacob, Your favored servant, by including him among the followers of Moses, peace be on them both, and blessed Your intimate beloved, Muhammad, may the blessings of Allah be upon him and his Household, in his offspring, offspring, and people. O Allah! Just as we were absent from that but we believe in it honestly and truly, So we beseech You to send Your benedictions upon Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad, to bless Muhammad and the household of Muhammad, and to have mercy on Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad with the most auspicious benedictions, blessings, and mercy that You sent to Abraham and the posterity of Abraham. Surely, You are Praiseworthy, Glorious, and Doer of what You will. You are Powerful over all things. \r\n\r\nYou may now beseech Almighty Allah to grant you your personal requests. Then, say the following:\r\n\r\nO Allah, in the name of this prayer and in the name of these Names which none knows their exegesis or their implicit meanings save You, (please) send Your blessings upon Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad, do to me that of which You are worthy, do not do to me what I deserve, forgive my sins—past and future, increase Your lawful sustenance for me, and save me from the trouble of wicked men, wicked neighbors, wicked companions, and wicked rulers. Verily, You have power over all that You will to do and You have full knowledge of all things. Respond to me, O Lord of the worlds. \r\n\r\nAccording to some copies of the supplication, the following statement is added before the latter portion:\r\n\r\nO Allah! O All-tender! O Bestower! O Fashioner of the heavens and the earth! O Lord of Majesty and Honor! O most Merciful of all those who show mercy! (O Allah! I beseech You in the name of this prayer)... \r\n\r\nShaykh al-Majlisi has quoted Sayyid Ibn Baqi as saying, in al-Misbah, that the following supplicatory prayer is advisably said after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\nO Allah! I beseech You in the name of this prayer and in the name of these Names which none knows their exegesis or interpretation and none knows their implicit or explicit meanings save You, to send Your blessings upon Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad and to provide me with the good of this world and the Next world. \r\n\r\nYou may then mention your need and continue as follows:\r\n\r\nDo to me that of which You are worthy but do not do to me what I deserve, and exact vengeance from... [so-and-so] \r\n\r\nYou may here mention the name of your enemy…\r\n\r\nforgive my sins—past and future, forgive my parents and all faithful believers—men and women, increase Your lawful sustenance for me, save me from the troubles of wicked men, wicked neighbors, wicked rulers, wicked companions, evil days, and evil hours, and exact vengeance for me on everyone who hatches secret plots against me, on everyone who oppresses me, seeks to do injustice to me, my wife, my children, my brothers, my neighbors, and my relatives among faithful men and women. Verily, You have power to do whatever You will to do and You have full knowledge of all things. Respond to me, O Lord of the worlds\r\n\r\nYou may then say the following:\r\n\r\nO Allah! In the name of this prayer, I beseech You to grant wealth and affluence to indigent faithful men and women, recovery and wellbeing to the sick faithful men and women, bliss and clemency to the living faithful men and women, remit the sins of, and have mercy on, the deceased faithful men and women, and arrange the return of all faithful travelers with safety and gain, by Your mercy, O Most Merciful of all those who show mercy. May Allah send blessings to our master Muhammad, the Seal of the Prophets, and upon his Household, the purified and send peace upon them in abundant measure. \r\n\r\nShaykh Ibn Fahad says that it is recommended to say the following prayer after Dua al-Simat:\r\n\r\nO Allah, I beseech You in the name of the sacredness of this prayer, the Names mentioned therein, and the explanation and deep meanings of these names that none comprehends save You... \r\n\r\nYou may now mention your personal needs."
}